85
86 (2) The nonlegislative members of the study
87 commission shall serve without compensation but may be
88 reimbursed for necessary expenses in attending meetings of
89 the study commission pursuant to the policies of their
90 respective appointing authority.
91 (g) Pursuant to Section 36-14-17.1, Code of Alabama
92 1975, the study commission shall provide to the Secretary of
93 State a notice of all meetings, the name of each member
94 serving on the study commission, and a copy of the final
95 report and any other documents produced by the study
96 commission throughout its duration.
